                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>B.H. Kibler; Spring Hill, Feb 29, '57.--Vind. please copy.</trailer>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Blair</ln>
                        <pf>Dr.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Kibler</ln>
                        <pf>B. H.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Very difficult to read (faint print). Seems to involve Blair attacking a
                    slave woman. This letter is not supportive of him</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>6</column>
                <head>For the Spectator</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>--In short, let women rule--you shall be well ruled.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>KATE KARELESS</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Very difficult to read (faint print) Seems to suggest that womenshould
                    serve on the town Council instead of men. More business would be accomplished,
                    more improvements made to the town.</summary>
            </div>
